args:
In the preliminaries, Valerio's rivals include
Picaro, the lazy scion of a well-regarded
restaurant, as well as a master Hinomotoan
chef named Mitsuba. As the competition heats
up, the prince and his friends set out with the
living vegetable Pipple to gather ingredients.
Now that the preliminaries have begun,\nour chefs and their helpers must each\ngather their own ingredients.
It's not enough for a chef to simply work\nwith ingredients selected by others—they\nmust know how to find their OWN!
Easy for him to say—he ain't the one\nwho has to go looking for ingredients\nin a fiend-infested forest!
I would've prepared way more if I'd known\nthis was gonna be the way of it.
Oho ho ho! Flustered already? My, my, my.
Y-you're the head chef at L'Amandier!\nThat's the greatest restaurant in the world!
What an eye you have, my untalented\nfriend! I am indeed Picaro, head chef\nand inheritor of L'Amandier.

Still, if this little rule change is enough
to make you break down, I suggest you
take up an easier career...like stirring
pottage! Oho! Oho ho ho ho!

But Picaro? Oho ho! Picaro has prepared
for any and all contingencies! I have a
pantry full of ingredients, plus a full staff
of sous chefs at my beck and call!

THAT is the secret to being a top-tier chef!
Surely you mewling bunch of table waiters
understand that? Ah, but perhaps Picaro
gives you too much credit. Oho ho ho!
By my copper saucepan! It's Valerio,\nthe wandering genius chef of legend!
Perhaps, dear boy, you would be good\nenough to explain what you meant when\nyou called my message ＂rot.＂
Money and status will not lead to victory\nin this place. Instead, skill and composure\nwill be the orders of the day.
Oho ho ho! You're certainly ARROGANT\nenough to be a genius, though I'm so\nfar failing to see the ＂genius＂ portion.
And yet, I hear you care for neither riches\nnor fame, no? If so, what brings you here\nto the Orichalcum Chef contest?
Only a simple dream, friend: I wish to feed\nthe people of the world until their\ntaste buds cry out in ecstasy.
Pah! What nonsense! What balderdash!\nSuch idle thoughts are beneath a common\ndishwasher, much less a chef!
Well, no matter. My ＂rot,＂ as you say, will\nmake steak tartare of your precious dream!
That guy seems fun at parties.
The genius Valerio going against the elite\nchef Picaro promises to be a most heated\ncompetition indeed.
In that case, let's help out so they can\nfocus on doing what they do best.
You would like to help? Excellent.\nIn that case, please deal with him.
Nimis need food badly...\nNimis about to die...
If I am to devote my attentions to cooking,\nI must leave him in your capable hands.\nFarewell, my new friends.
But if this dragon gets hungry again,\nhe'll surely run rampant! What are we\ngoing to do, {player_name}?!
NIMIS NEED FOOD BADLY!\nNIMIS ABOUT TO DIE!
Against all odds, the party manages to keep Nimis\ncalm for a short while. And later that night...
That scream came from the kitchen!
Let us make for it apace!
Get out of my cooking pot, you...you...\nyou whatever you are!
Oh, it's just a lady and a...um...
Er, is that a potato with eyes?\n...Real eyes, I mean.
We heard a scream. Is something wrong?
This little...THING showed up out of\nnowhere and jumped into my pot!
Now my special dashi is ruined and\nI have to make the entire thing over.
I am quite sorry to hear that, madam.\nEr, but what IS this creature, anyway?
I do. This is Pipple, a vegetable.
The vegetables I am familiar with\ndo not move about or make noises.
Ah, but just look at him. Pure vegetable.
He appeared before me while I was out in\nthe woods. I told him to go away, but...\nWell, as you can see, he didn't listen.
And then, I take my eyes off of him for one\nsecond, and look at the ruckus he causes.
Out of my pot, you! Shoo! Bad parsnip!\nUuugh, this dashi is totally ruined now.
So you're a chef too, yeah? I mean,\nsince you're in the kitchen making soup\nand all, it seems a pretty safe guess.
Oh, sorry, I forgot to introduce myself.\nI'm Mitsuba, a chef from Hinomoto.
If I didn't know better, I'd swear this\nPipple thing WANTS to be eaten.

Hey! You! The tall drink of water there!
If you're gonna make a pet out of a
vegetable, take some responsibility
for it and help me out here!
I wouldn't call him my PET exactly, but...\nYes, well. My apologies for the trouble.\nYou apologize as well, Pipple.
*sigh* Oh, I suppose it's all right.\nThis dashi was just a test batch, anyway.
But don't expect it to go like this in the\ncompetition, Mr. Wandering Genius.\nI'm not gonna lose to you!
How very competitive of you to say so.
No apologies here! We both wanna be\nthe best, which makes us rivals.

So then! I heard you talking to that gasbag
Picaro earlier. Sounds like you're in this
contest because you want to bring tasty
food to everyone in the world.
Well, I've got an equally important dream\nin mind, which is why I'm gonna WIN!
Anyway, bye for now, Mr. Genius.\nCatch you in the Hungerdome!
Three worthy adversaries,\neach vying for the top...
It matters not—I will be the winner.\nBut right now, we have a more\npressing concern. ...Pipple!
I know not if your true aim is to be eaten,\nbut you must stop interfering with people.
So if you insist on being here, be useful\ninstead of simply getting in the way.\nFor example, you can gather ingredients.
Oh, he's got a fork!\nGuess he's really raring to go!
Sounds like we're going ingredient\nhunting. Come on, Pipple!
(I don't care how much of a genius Valerio\nis, or what his dream might be—I am NOT\ngoing to lose this competition!)
Oho ho! Go on, now! Eat your fill!
My cooking is divinity itself, no?\nCome, now! Eat all you can!
(Picaro is feeding that hungry dragon.\n...But WHY is he doing it?!)
